main event: An object was observed in the sky on 12 Aug 1948, identified and confirmed to be Venus.
interesting points: The sighting took place over a span of several hours from 1130 to 1524 EST., The object's shape was circular., The color of the object was silver., The object was reported to be at an altitude of 20,000 to 40,000 feet., The direction of the object's movement was southwest.
witness description: No witnesses specified in the document.
